FT  17 SEP 93 / UK Company News: British Fittings back in black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE STEPS taken last year to restructure management and control costs have
put British Fittings Group back in the black in the six months to June 30.
Despite continuing adverse trading conditions, the group turned in pre-tax
profits of Pounds 672,000, against Pounds 1.02m losses last time. The
results have been prepared according to FRS 3 and comparatives restated.
Turnover in continuing businesses fell 6 per cent to Pounds 34.8m (Pounds
36.96m), but operating profits on these businesses rose by 32 per cent to
Pounds 1.43m (Pounds 1.09m). The group's activities cover pipeline equipment
distribution, high pressure water products and non-ferrous metals
distribution.
Interest charge for the half year was lower at Pounds 762,000 (Pounds 1.28m)
and after tax of Pounds 70,000 (nil), earnings per share were 1.71p (5.11p
losses). The interim dividend has been raised by 50 per cent to 0.75p
(0.5p).
