<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Davis Service ahead at Pounds 8.47m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PRE-TAX profits at Davis Service Group, the now reorganised and refocused
business services concern, rose from Pounds 8.03m to Pounds 8.47m in the six
months to June 30.
The results for the first half of 1992 were skewed by a Pounds 2.45m
contribution from Godfrey Davis (Contract Hire), sold in April 1992 for
Pounds 5.75m, and a net interest charge of Pounds 2.53m, which was mostly
the result of the large amount of 'back-to-back' borrowings incurred by the
contract hire business. Net interest payable this time came to Pounds
456,000.
Gearing at the period-end was 23 per cent on borrowings of Pounds 25.5m,
Pounds 18m of which were built up by the Pounds 52m acquisition in May of
HSS Hire Services Group from John Mowlem.
The 170-strong HSS chain contributed Pounds 699,000 to continuing operating
profits of Pounds 8.93m (Pounds 8.11m) and Pounds 10.2m to continuing
turnover of Pounds 119m (Pounds 101.7m). It is expected to grow at the rate
of 20 outlets a year. Total group turnover came to Pounds 127.7m (Pounds
124.7m).
Mr George Boyle, finance director, said as had been foreseen, demand in the
group's markets had remained flat, making for increased competition and
pressure on margins.
Earnings per share advanced to 6.51p (6.39p) and the interim dividend is
held at 2.73p.
</TEXT>
