FT  17 SEP 93 / Technology: Putting videos in the picture - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
For those would-be cinematographers with 8mm camcorders, the Korean
electronics company Goldstar has introduced a simpler way of transferring
recordings from 8mm to VHS format so that the film can be viewed like an
ordinary video.
The RDD10i machine is a traditional VHS remote control VCR but with an extra
slot for 8mm tapes. By inserting the recorded 8mm tape and a blank VHS tape
the reording can be simply transferred. The system also includes basic film
editing capabilities to help produce a more professional film. The RDD10i
costs Pounds 629.99. Goldstar: South Korea, 2 787 1114; UK, 0753 691888.
