<HEADLINE>
FT  17 SEP 93 / Second vote
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   RABAT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Moroccans vote again today to elect 111 members of parliament after an
earlier vote for the other 222 members failed to produce a majority for any
party, Reuter reports from Rabat.
The indirect vote will select one third of the Chamber of Representatives
which is due to meet for the first time next month for a six-year mandate.
</TEXT>
