<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / Zaire facing its 'worst human rights crisis'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AMNESTY International accuses Zaire's security forces today of appalling
human rights violations and urges the international community to intervene
before there is a complete breakdown of law and order, Reuter reports from
London.
Amnesty says in a report that Zaire is facing its worst human rights crisis
since the end of the civil war in the mid-1960s. It cites 'ruthless
brutality of government security forces . . . who have murdered or tortured
thousands of civilians and members of the peaceful political opposition'.
The report, 'Zaire: Violence against Democracy', calls on the international
community to devise ways to end the crisis.
