<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / International Company News: Federal Express recovers in
first quarter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our New York Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FEDERAL Express, the biggest overnight delivery company in the US, cut
operating losses in its international operation by Dollars 24m to Dollars
33.2m in the three months to end August, helping to treble net income
compared with same quarter last year.
After-tax earnings for the first quarter of its financial year were Dollars
32.9m, up from Dollars 10.1m a year ago before the effect of accounting
changes.
Mr Frederick Smith, chairman, said the results were encouraging, but warned:
'Because last year's first-quarter results were disappointing, the
year-on-year comparison for the rest of this fiscal year may not be as
dramatic.'
Future earnings growth will depend on further revenue gains in the
international priority sector, which were up 17 per cent in the first
quarter.
