FT  16 SEP 93 / International Company News: CSFB in pay scheme to unite
group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CS FIRST BOSTON, the investment banking arm of Switzerland's CS Holding, is
developing a company-wide compensation scheme as part of its efforts to meld
into a single global investment bank.
Compensation has been a controversial subject at the firm, which operated
until recently as three separate regional entities tied by revenue-sharing
agreements.
Mr Alan Wheat, chief operating officer, said the system might not be in
place until next year. 'Measurement systems in this company are not what you
would want them to be,' he said, adding that not all the issues surrounding
compensation had been resolved.
Mr Wheat said the arrangements might prompt further departures from the
firm, which suffered a number of defections earlier this year. 'I think
there are other people who may well leave,' he said.
