<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Oliver Group cuts loss to Pounds 2.24m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OLIVER Group, the footwear retailer, made progress in cutting its losses in
the first half of 1993 with a fall from Pounds 4.87m to Pounds 2.24m
pre-tax.
Turnover fell 11.5 per cent to Pounds 33.2m (Pounds 37.5m) the result of
branch closures. During the period 34 were closed with a further 16 poor
performing branches earmarked for the second half.
The pre-tax figure was helped by cost cutting and a lower interest charge of
Pounds 557,000 (Pounds 1.26m).
The company has announced the intended closure of Brick Studio, the
remaining non-footwear activity. Completion is scheduled for the fourth
quarter of this year.
Losses per share came out at 8.86p (19.28p).
