<HEADLINE>
FT  16 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Savoy loss unchanged at Pounds 1.75m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SKAPINKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SAVOY HOTEL announced an unchanged first half pre-tax loss of Pounds 1.75m
and said it had not benefited from the improvement in the economy or from
last September's devaluation of sterling, writes Michael Skapinker
The loss for the six months to June 30 was on turnover up 3 per cent to
Pounds 37.8m. The group, whose hotels include the Savoy, the Connaught and
Claridge's, said its operating costs rose 3.5 per cent to Pounds 36m,
largely due to an increase in sales and marketing expenditure.
Mr Giles Shepard, managing director, said: 'Despite certain aspects of the
economy improving, such improvements as there were did not benefit the
company, nor were the effects of last September's devaluation of sterling
reflected in an increasing number of foreign visitors to our hotels and
restaurants.'
The group's pre-tax loss was limited by an increase in investment income
from Pounds 68,000 to Pounds 587,000. This included a Pounds 555,000 profit
on the sale of the Savoy Theatre's investment portfolio. At the trading
level, the loss increased to Pounds 1.6m Pounds 1.15m.
Losses were 4p (3.5p) per A share and 2p (1.7p) per B share.
</TEXT>
